'''Bus to Nowhere''' is a PC-only cooperative collect-a-thon adventure [[Special:MyLanguage/:Category:Game worlds|game world]] containing events, biomes, boss fights, and multiple endings. The world has a capacity of up to 40 users and is centered around you and NPC '''passengers''' on the ''Time Bus''.

== Overview ==
The Time Bus starts in the Grass '''biome''', with 0.0 miles on the odometer. As time goes on, the mileage on the odometer will increase. The Bus can drive itself, but will speed up if a user is standing or sitting near the driver's seat.

Every so often, an event (if enabled) will occur, which can increase the chance of you collecting '''items''' to bring onto the bus. Some items provide functionality, while some items are mere props. The outcome of your journey, and passengers and items that are unlocked, are dependent on the actions taken by you, and other users in the instance.

=== The Time Bus ===
The Time Bus is a triple-decker bus, with a small balcony on the back of the second floor, a bathroom on the first floor, and a hidden engine room which can only be accessed during night time. Over time, more passengers will occupy the Time Bus when certain requirements are met.

