== Events ==
{| class="wikitable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed"
|+List of events
!Event
!Effect
|-
|Bus Stops
|The bus ceases movement, in front of a bus stop. There are multiple bus stops in Bus to Nowhere. Some may have unique items, NPCs, posters, or scribblings etched onto its foundation.
|-
|Story Machine
|A unique bus stop that can tell you more information or lore about an item, when placed onto its scanner.
|-
|Thunderstorm
|Rain and thunder surround the bus. A bolt of lightning strikes the roof of the bus.
|-
|Lemonade Stand
|The bus stops in front of a lemonade stand, featuring an NPC offering suspicious cans of lemonade. You can take the lemonade with you.
|-
|Flood
|The bus stops movement, and the first and second floor of the bus is submerged with water.
|-
|Stairway to Heaven
|A heavenly stairway appears on the third floor of the Time Bus for a short while. An item appears at the top of the stairs. It is recommended to use a Speed Coil to ascend the staircase before it disappears.
|-
|UFO
|A UFO hovers over the Time Bus for a short while, and pulls in users with its tractor beam. Moai statues should be brought inside the UFOs to unlock more secrets.
|-
|Police Chase
|A police car chases the Time Bus, with sirens blaring. The police car can be neutralized with many of the effective ranged or melee weapons. If this event happens again after a police car is neutralized, a second police car will follow in pursuit. If neutralized, three cars come for the third event.
|-
|Cabin
|The bus stops in front of an abandoned cabin. The cabin has two floors. A teddy bear can be collected on the second floor.
|-
|Hot Tub
|A hot tub appears on the top floor of the Time Bus. During this event, there is an invisible 'pocket dimension' (called the '''Have Dimension''') when jumping northeast off of the front-right side of the bus, containing a collectible GPS.
|-
|Among Us
|Among Us characters spring out of the vents in mass, overwhelming the first floor of the Time Bus.
|-
|Power Surge
|The bus temporarily stops movements, and loses lighting. However, the television can still be used. In rare cases, a creature may attack the bus, leaving behind a collectable Sweeper Hook on the back side of the Time Bus.
|-
|Freddy
|The bus powers off, similar to the Power Surge event, except an image of Freddy, from Five Nights at Freddy's appears on the windshield.
|-
|Wall
|This event is exclusive to The Sanctum biome. The bus crashes into two walls.
|-
|Beach
|This event is exclusive to the Beach biome. The bus stops at a beach, featuring a sun-bathing 'Purple Guy' NPC.
|-
|Pavillion
|This event is exclusive to the Cliff biome. A pavillion appears on a platform, perched off the edge of the cliff. A GPS can be collected, and the 'DarkGray' NPC appears.
|-
|Sewer
|This event is exclusive to the Roofed Forest biome. The bus stops in front of a dark sewer grate. A flashlight can be collected. Walking deep into the sewer grate, makes the user fall through its floor, eventually ending up in the engine room below the bus.
|-
|Blizzard
|This event is exclusive to cold biomes. A blizzard surrounds the bus, fogging up the windshield.
|-
|The Black Forest
|There are four unique events to The Black Forest biome.
Phase one, involves a bird floating around the bus, and in front of the windshield. Interacting with the bird makes it attack the bus. Not acknowledging the bird makes an egg appear on the bus, and sends The Black Forest into phase two.
Phase two, a giant bird-like creature with several legs, dubbed "Big Bird", chases the bus and rams into it. When the bus powers down, running northeast of the bus leads the user to a giant egg. Collecting the second egg takes it to the bus, and sends The Black Forest into phase three.
Phase three, a bird with a judgement scale hovers above the roof of the bus. The user must jump onto the higher scale to balance it evenly. Evenly balancing the scales, grants the user the third and final egg, sending The Black Forest to phase four.
Phase four is a boss fight, facing "Apocalypse Bird". Making Apocalypse Bird destroy each of the three eggs, using its various attacks clears the boss fight.
|}

